# Local PostgreSQL Connectivity (Docker) — Fast Reuse Guide

## **Overview**

When `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080` (see [`.env.local`](mdc:.env.local)), the Spring Boot API reads/writes **local Docker PostgreSQL**, not Supabase. Use this rule to connect and run SQL (tenant updates, event date fixes, counts, verification) without rediscovering credentials each session.

**Related rules (do not duplicate):**
- Bulk import/export: [database_export_import_vpc_local.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/database_export_import_vpc_local.mdc)
- Table/column conventions: [database_schema_guidelines.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/database_schema_guidelines.mdc)
- `pg_dump` / schema rebuild: [documentation/INSERT_TABLE_BULK_SQL_REORDERING_AND_PG_DUMP_GUIDE.md](mdc:documentation/INSERT_TABLE_BULK_SQL_REORDERING_AND_PG_DUMP_GUIDE.md)

