## **Which database to use (decision tree)**

```
Is NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL pointing to localhost:8080?
├─ YES → Use LOCAL Docker Postgres (this rule)
└─ NO  → Remote RDS / Supabase (do NOT use local Docker; use ops/VPN/RDS credentials)

Does .env.local contain DATABASE_URL / DIRECT_URL (Supabase)?
└─ Used by some Next.js/Prisma tooling — NOT the same DB as local Spring Boot on :8080
```

| Context | Database target |
|--------|------------------|
| Local dev (`localhost:8080` API) | Docker → `event_site_manager_db` |
| `.env.local` `DATABASE_URL` (Supabase) | Cloud Supabase — separate from local API data |
| Batch import script | Docker → `event_site_manager_db` (often `event_site_admin` user) |

