## **CRITICAL: database name is NOT `postgres`**

The default database `postgres` exists but **application tables live in `event_site_manager_db`**.

```powershell
# ❌ WRONG — empty or no event_details
docker exec event_site_manager_db-postgresql-1 psql -U postgres -d postgres -c "\dt event_details"

# ✅ DO — application data
docker exec event_site_manager_db-postgresql-1 psql -U postgres -d event_site_manager_db -c "\dt event_details"
```

**Discovery if unsure:**

```powershell
docker exec event_site_manager_db-postgresql-1 psql -U postgres -d postgres -c "\l"
```

Look for database **`event_site_manager_db`**.

