## **Worked example: move future events to past (2025)**

**Verified pattern** (local Docker, tenant `mosc_malankara_orthodox_2`):

```powershell
# 1) Preview
docker exec event_site_manager_db-postgresql-1 psql -U postgres -d event_site_manager_db -c "
SELECT id, title, start_date, end_date
FROM event_details
WHERE tenant_id = 'mosc_malankara_orthodox_2'
  AND start_date >= CURRENT_DATE
ORDER BY start_date;
"

# 2) Update — shift start/end year to 2025 (preserves month/day)
docker exec event_site_manager_db-postgresql-1 psql -U postgres -d event_site_manager_db -c "
BEGIN;
UPDATE event_details
SET
  start_date = start_date - ((EXTRACT(YEAR FROM start_date)::integer - 2025) * INTERVAL '1 year'),
  end_date = CASE
    WHEN end_date IS NOT NULL
      THEN end_date - ((EXTRACT(YEAR FROM end_date)::integer - 2025) * INTERVAL '1 year')
    ELSE NULL
  END,
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE tenant_id = 'mosc_malankara_orthodox_2'
  AND start_date >= CURRENT_DATE;
COMMIT;
"

# 3) Verify zero future events remain
docker exec event_site_manager_db-postgresql-1 psql -U postgres -d event_site_manager_db -c "
SELECT COUNT(*) AS remaining_future
FROM event_details
WHERE tenant_id = 'mosc_malankara_orthodox_2'
  AND start_date >= CURRENT_DATE;
"
```

After data changes, refresh the Next.js app or invalidate homepage cache if hero/events look stale.

